section.section:
The venue of the following actions is in the county where all or any portion of the subject matter of the action is located:
Partition of real estate;
Enforcement of a charge or lien on land;
Eminent domain;
Trespass to land; and
Waste.

Except as provided in paragraphs (2) and (3) of this subsection, the venue for a proceeding for adoption of an individual who is physically within this State or subject to the jurisdiction of an equity court is in a county where:
The petitioner is domiciled;
The petitioner has resided for at least 90 days next preceding the filing of the petition;
A licensed child placement agency having legal or physical custody of the individual is located;
The individual is domiciled, if the individual is related to the petitioner by blood or marriage or is an adult; or
An equity court has continuing jurisdiction over the custody of the individual.
